"The US, undoubtedly, declared an economic war against Russia and they are waging this war. Yes, de facto this is exactly what it is," Peskov told the state-backed news agency TASS.

The Kremlin official said Moscow will do “what in the best way corresponds to our interests,” without elaborating any possible retaliatory sanctions.

Earlier on Wednesday, a Russian foreign ministry official said that Moscow was working on a set of counter sanctions that will be “swift, thoughtful and sensitive for those it addresses.”

