Evacuation Of Civilians From Sumy Will Continue On Wednesday

Evacuation of civilians from the city of Sumy in north-east Ukraine will continue on Wednesday, according to the region’s governor Dmytro Zhyvytsky.

Reuters reports that around 5,000 people were evacuated from the city on Tuesday after Russia and Ukraine agreed to a brief ceasefire to allow a humanitarian corridor. Additionally, around 1,000 cars were also able to leave the city.

The corridor connecting Sumy to Poltava in central Ukraine was the only corridor where a ceasefire remained in place on Tuesday and both sides accused each other of violating it in Kharkiv, Mariupol and Chernihiv.

Zhyvytsky also added that a residential block in Sumy was bombed overnight, with one bomb killing 22 civilians.

