PepsiCo and Coca-Cola announced Tuesday they will suspend business in Russia, and McDonald’s and Starbucks are temporarily shuttering Russian stores, as a growing list of American consumer brands leave Russia amid the invasion of Ukraine.

McDonald’s said it will continue to pay its Russia-based employees after closing 847 stores, and Starbucks says the licensee that runs its Russian shops will “provide support” to employees despite the closures. Yum! Brands—the parent company of KFC, Taco Bell and Pizza Hut—also announced Tuesday it has “suspended all investment and restaurant development in Russia,” though it didn’t specify whether existing stores will remain open, noting that the vast majority of its 1,000 Russia-based KFCs and 50 Pizza Huts are run by independent operators.

