Roughly Four In Five Americans Support Ban On Russian Oil, Poll Shows

On the same day President Joe Biden announced a decision Tuesday to ban the import of Russian oil and natural gas as further punishment for Russia’s invasion of Ukraine, a Wall Street Journal poll found 79% of surveyed Americans support the ban and just 13% oppose it—despite the uptick in prices at the pump.

The poll pulled from 529 registered voters over the last four days. Left-leaning voters were more in favor of the move, with 88% of surveyed Democrats saying they favored the ban compared to 77% of surveyed Republicans and 72% of surveyed voters who said they would support the re-election of Donald Trump.

Gas prices in the U.S. surpassed their all-time highest average price Tuesday, reaching $4.17 a gallon and exceeding costs last seen during the 2008 recession. Read more about why Americans will “feel the pain” of these high costs for a while here .

