Market Reaction To Oil Bans: Gas Prices Skyrocket, Stocks Continue Dip

Average gas prices reached a record high of $4.17 per gallon Tuesday, a 55-cent increase from last week, as reports of the United States and United Kingdom’s impending Russian oil bans surfaced. Patrick De Haan, head of petroleum analysis at fuel savings company GasBuddy, predicted average gas prices may soon near $4.50 in a statement.

Stocks dipped slightly in early Tuesday trading, with the Dow Jones Industrial Average, S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite all falling between 0.3% and 0.7%, building off of significant Monday losses. Edward Moya, senior market analyst at Oanda, predicted “ultimately the economy will fall into a recession at some point over the next 24 months” due to Russia’s war on Ukraine.

