The United Kingdom will ban Russian oil imports, according to Politico and Bloomberg , with British Prime Minister Boris Johnson expected to announce the move Tuesday, according to Politico. Both outlets report the embargo will be gradual and take place over the course of several months—and the ban does not include Russian gas.

The United States will soon announce a blanket ban on all Russian energy imports, numerous outlets reported Tuesday morning. The European Union released a plan Tuesday to cut EU demand for Russian gas by two-thirds by the end of 2022 and make the EU energy “independent from Russian fossil fuels well before 2030,” but isn’t expected to announce a ban on Russian oil due to opposition from several member countries, most notably Germany.

